This paper discusses the evaluation of research and researchers, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The use of the journal impact factor (JIF) is a common practice in the field of digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR) for evaluating the quality of research publications. The study also involves the analysis of citation data, which is relevant to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Additionally, the study may be of interest to researchers in the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI) who are concerned with the impact of publications on the network structure. Overall, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CR, cs.CY, and cs.SI, in descending order of likelihood.
